2.2 Word frequency distribution

cat_word_count <- tokenized.df %>%
    unnest(word) %>%
    count(cat, word) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    filter(!str_detect(word, "[a-zA-Z0-9]+")) %>%
    anti_join(stopWords)
Joining, by = "word"
Column `word` joining character vector and factor, coercing into character vector
compared <- cat_word_count %>%
    filter(n>1) %>%
    spread(cat, n, fill = 0) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate_each(funs((. + 1) / sum(. + 1)), -word) %>%
    mutate(logratio = log2(early / lat)) %>%
    arrange(desc(logratio))
`mutate_each()` is deprecated.
Use `mutate_all()`, `mutate_at()` or `mutate_if()` instead.
To map `funs` over a selection of variables, use `mutate_at()`

frequency <- cat_word_count %>%
    group_by(cat) %>%
    mutate(proportion = n/sum(n)) %>%
    select(-n) %>%
    spread(cat, proportion) %>%
    na.omit()
